 "summary_en": "Archived planning records place the Louise M. Davies Symphony Hall within the Civic Center performing-arts complex. A 1994 Civic Center cultural-facilities study lists the hall's seating capacity as 2,743, identifies it as home of the San Francisco Symphony under War Memorial trustee control, and notes \"approximately 30 days per year are available for rental.\" A 1997 School of the Arts environmental report records an evening performance drawing 2,420 in the \"2,743-seat\" hall, and a 1986 newspaper announces an \"East Meets West\" concert held there. Davies Hall is operated by the War Memorial (WAR) department, whose FY2025 budget is about $30M; the file records 60 building permits totaling about $10.6M in declared cost, including a 1992 acoustic-improvement permit declared at $5,000,000.",
